reserved to the state from 19 to 8, reports Damian Fraser in Mexico City.
Under Mexican law, only the state-owned Petroleos Mexicanos (Pemex) can make
basic petrochemicals, defined as those chemicals that are the result of the
first chemcical or physical transformation from gas or oil. This definition
has proved to be elastic, and the number of basic petrochemicals has
steadily been reduced over the past six years, according to political rather
than scientific considerations.
