<TEXT>
A NIGHT-LONG rocket duel between rebel forces and pro-government troops
ended early yesterday with defence ministry officials claiming to have
repulsed the attack, AP reports from Kabul. For a week rebels loyal to
fundamentalist rebel Gulbuddin Hekmatyar have been pounding the capital with
rockets, killing an estimated 1,000 people.
