<HEADLINE>
FT  17 AUG 92 / Final phase of British Library project started
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Rounding off: work has started on the new British Library's amphitheatre as
part of the final phase of the Pounds 450m project. This phase includes the
new reading room and the six-storey, glass-walled tower which will house the
King George III collection of books and manuscripts. Construction of the
building began 10 years ago, on the site of the former goods yard for St
Pancras station in Euston Road, London. Some reading rooms are due to open
in 1994 but the project will not be completed until 1996. The new library
will allow the public access to 12m volumes and more than 1m visitors are
expected each year.
