FT  17 AUG 92 / Construction Contracts: Expansion at London hospital
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A 13.7m contract to construct two buildings in the grounds of Hammersmith
Hospital in west London has been awarded to MOWLEM SOUTH EAST, a division of
John Mowlem Construction.
The larger of the two is an eight-storey 9,500 sq metre clinical research
building for the Medical Research Council. The building will have six
storeys of fully fitted laboratories for research into the basic science of
disease, with two storeys of plant above.
The second is a three-storey 3,500 sq metre cancer centre for The Hammer
Cancer Trust. This will have treatment rooms and wards grouped around a
central atrium.
