FT  17 AUG 92 / Parcels sell-offs may be linked
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID OWEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE GOVERNMENT is considering co-ordinating aspects of the sale of the two
parcels businesses that it is to privatise.
Mr Michael Heseltine, trade and industry secretary, and Mr John MacGregor,
transport secretary, are to discuss the timing of the disposals, which will
transfer both Parcelforce, the Post Office's delivery service, and British
Rail's parcels division to the private sector.
The level of co-ordination, however, is thought unlikely to extend to
appointing the same teams of advisers to handle both sales.
Though nothing has been ruled out, it is expected that traditional
inter-departmental rivalries may limit the extent of co-operation. British
Rail is primarily Mr MacGregor's responsibility, while the Post Office is Mr
Heseltine's.
