the enlarged capital with Stratagem having 1.65m or 11.2 per cent. The
Takeover Panel has agreed to waive any obligation for Mr Morton to make an
offer for the company, subject to the transactions being approved at an EGM.
On completion of the placing Mr Morton will become chairman of MMI and could
eventually make it a shell company for his private interests.
MMI also announced a pre-tax loss of Pounds 383,000 for the 14 months to
February 28, against profits of Pounds 317,000 for 1990.
There is no final dividend (1p) making the total for the period 0.25p
(1.25p). MMI's shares closed at 7p, down 3 1/2 p.
