FT  15 AUG 92 / Kabul troops repulse rebels
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Troops loyal to the Islamic government in Kabul have repulsed violent
assaults by rebel mujahideen fighters yesterday, agencies report from Kabul.
However Gen. Majid Khan told reporters that he anticipated another round of
fighting as forces loyal to firebrand fundamentalist Gulbudddin Hekmatyar
prepared to make another bid for the battle-weary capital.
'He will try again. But we won't let him,' said Gen. Khan, without
elaborating how government soldiers proposed stopping him.
After more than a week of relentless rocketing, the capital was quiet
yesterday. But the bloodletting injured hundreds of people and left no water
or electricity and meager medical supplies.
